race.comment: BOOM BREAK (1) led and just missed fresh then broke through for the maiden win last time over 1100m at Ipswich. Fitter again and going well. Expected to take catching again. STATEMENT OF TRUTH (3) looks a big danger on the nice return when beaten less than a length. Kept fresh for this and worth noting did win only other try second-up. THIEM (8) was a little disappointing two back on the Sunny Coast but has placed three times either side. At peak fitness and overdue for a win. Raced on speed and just missed in the latest and among the main hopes again. GRAND CRUSADER (5) resumed from a long break at Kilcoy and fought on well for a close-up second. Doesn't win out of turn but encouraging fresh and worth following up. JE REVE (6) was on the heels of THIEM last time and is a top three chance.
